# Known divergence (by design): the libpq fast-path FunctionCall protocol is
# explicitly rejected by the multigateway (ErrorResponse 0A000 + ReadyForQuery,
# session kept alive) — see go/common/pgprotocol/server/conn.go and the pgproto
# function_call patch. psql's \lo_unlink / \lo_import / \lo_export use libpq's
# large-object API, which drives fast-path, so those commands error here; the
# SQL that depended on their side effects then sees empty results. lo_import /
# lo_export additionally hit the pooler's server-filesystem-access rejection.
# Everything else in the test (SQL-level lo_* functions) works and the session
# survives each rejection. Fast-path passthrough is tracked as future work
# (pg_dump with blobs / JDBC LargeObjectManager would revive it).
